The paper discusses a method for eliciting probabilities from a domain expert for use in belief networks. This involves combining both qualitative and quantitative information. The paper is likely to fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) due to the focus on probabilistic reasoning and uncertainty. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) due to the potential applications of belief networks in these areas. Finally, the paper may also fall under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) due to the focus on eliciting information from domain experts.
